Business Rules

These are the rules that the backend must enforce automatically. The frontend should not be responsible for these - they must be enforced server-side.

•	A student cannot have two internship placements with overlapping dates.
•	A student can only submit one weekly log per week per placement.
•	A log cannot be submitted after the submission deadline.
•	A supervisor can only review logs of students assigned to them.
•	An academic supervisor can only evaluate each student once per placement.
•	Evaluation criteria weights must always add up to exactly 100%.
•	The final evaluation score is computed automatically. It is never entered manually.
•	Every state change on a log must be saved to the history with who made the change, when, and why.
•	Once a log is APPROVED, it cannot be edited, deleted, or have its state changed by anyone.

	
